    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:8px;">What you can try yourself &mdash; and what you can&rsquo;t.</h2>
    <p style="font-size:15px;color:var(--color-ink-mute);margin:0 0 8px;">Self-fix for C-series is more constrained than for other error families. The reason: <strong>repeated repair attempts on a corrupted file typically worsen the corruption</strong>. The steps below should be tried once each, in order. If they don&rsquo;t resolve the error, do not repeat them &mdash; escalate before damage progresses.</p>
